result.execSummary:
The defendant Billy Gene Brooks was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Credit Card-Fraudulent Use (<=$2500) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime, Habitual Criminality, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.41(5)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Billy Gene Brooks in court with attorney John Thaddeus Wasielewski.  Defendant Billy Gene Brooks in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.

Court WITHHELD sentence and places defendant on PROBATION for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions:
- AODA assessment and follow all recommendations for treatment; inpatient treatment at an appropriate treatment center
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended by the agent
-Maintain absolute sobriety
-Defendant shall not possess or consume any illegal drugs at any time and not possess or consume any other illegal substances at any time
-Defendant to submit to random urine screens and breathalyzer
-Seek and maintain employment
-Obey all probation conditions
-Defendant to pay all supervision fees
-Defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay all applicable surcharges and assessments during term of Probation
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments during term of probation
-No contact with any firearms 

Court advises defendant of his appellate rights

Defendant changes his plea to NO CONTEST.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, jury instructions and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Defendant to provide a DNA sample.  Case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 19.
